Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{}, sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, zest and halve the @lemon{1/2}. Chop the @tomato{1%medium} into 1cm chunks.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Put the @fresh pesto{32%g} into a #medium bowl{} and add a squeeze of lemon juice. Mix in the @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing, then set aside.

Pat the @salmon fillets{2} dry with kitchen paper. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Lay the fish skin-side down, onto a lined baking tray.

When the potatoes have ~{12%minutes} left, bake the fish on the middle shelf for ~{10-15%minutes} until cooked.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, pop a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the @olive oil{1%tsp} for the salsa.

Once hot, add the chopped tomato and cook until just warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Gently stir in the garlic and lemon zest and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}. Squeeze in some lemon juice and season with salt and pepper.

Taste and season again if needed, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to your pesto dressing and toss to coat.

Transfer the salmon to your plates and spoon over the warm tomato salsa.

Serve with the rosemary potatoes and pesto salad alongside. Enjoy!